o I'd rather them not seeing my 5 resists out of 7 on the reavers.  <p><center><a href="http://www.packetlost.com"><img src="http://www.packetlost.com/ho/eq/xaxsig.jpg"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyueh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yueh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 1:33:45 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1> On all of my nukes I use a macro that basically does a <br>
<br>
&quot;/g nuking that damn %t for 840 points... I hope.&quot;<br>
<br>
That way I get lots of &quot;Wow!  How many of those can you cast?&quot; questions and none of the chiding when I hit for 2 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 1:36:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1> No offense Yueh but those macros drive me crazy. The important macros IMO are those involving snares, heals, debuffs, mezzes and calls for help. I'm sure there are more, but a simple macro stating &quot;nuke'n mob %t for 1120 damage&quot; does nothing but annoy people like me.<br>
<br>
EDIT: added substance to my original comment <p><b><font face="Tahoma" size="2" color="#0000FF">[55 Evoker] VortexTwin 
<Horizons></font></b></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uvortextwin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VortexTwin</A> at: 8/14/01 1:38:25 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyueh.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yueh</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 1:56:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1> I only use it for the main nuke.  It really doesn't create very much spam.  If someone complains I'll turn it off but so far no one has.  In comparison to the rangers and monks I've grouped with the spam contribution is downright negligible <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uklithor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klithor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 3:49:24 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.deepwell.com/~dcrooks/images/Klithor.JPG WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1> Id love to have our damage shown. I think that alone could make us more group friendly than anything else. Look at how much rogues are loved now that everyone knows the damage they can do. <p><i>Klithor<i><Br>
Wizard of the 48th circle<Br>
Member of the "Unbroken"<Br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uknolanncaelestis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Knolann Caelestis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 4:20:09 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re:</span><hr size=1> Hrm, I'd be worried that since our damage comes in bigger but less frequent clumps that we would take more crap for resists than we would get praise. Still, it would be pretty cool for them to see those triple 600 hits with my tears heh. <br>
<br>
I remember once some mage was trying to solo a frog in Seb but got 2 at entrance. He died (didn't ask for help and was too late to realize) with one mob down maybe to 75-80% health.<br>
<br>
Anyway, a group that had been looking for 2 (one needed to be a enchanter) and a few /LFGs (including me) jumped on the frogs. I took both kills (even got a jacinth hehe), and next thing I know I'm invited to their group (after /lfg for about 5 minutes next to them). Yeah, I'm guessing they got a better idea of my damage there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uikeya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ikeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 4:30:34 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Subject Needed... I think? All these blasted re: blank space</span><hr size=1> Macros suck and drive me crazy. Sure, I can understand seeing &quot;Complete Heal incoming on &lt;Insertstupidtanknamethatisasstupidasminehere&gt;&quot; would make them feel more 'secure.' But then they lack faith in their healer! Same with shamans and druids. &quot;%T slowed!&quot; &quot;%T snared!&quot; Hello! I think they'll know if its been slowed by rate of attack and whether or not it runs! Frankly, IMO people who use macros for reasons other than pure roleplay are just adding more lag to my already fragile and unstable bandwidth.<br>
<br>
Don't know how many of you saw it, but someone (Rombus maybe? Forget who) posted a picture of an Eye of Zomm resisting Fetter... thats the last thing the group needs to see.<br>
<br>
-Ikeya <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uactinicpercussive.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Actinic Percussive</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 5:08:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Subject Needed... I think? All these blasted re: blank s</span><hr size=1> In my opinion, you need macros for one thing: charm. There's no success message.<br>
<br>
For everything else it's reported anyway; if you simply must see it in blue before you believe it, use a highlighter on your screen.<br>
<br>
(How can you possibly have a roleplaying macro? Roleplaying inna can? I don't get it.)<br>
<br>
I suppose tanks can have their little incoming keys to peck, and very occasionally the 'healing xxx' button saves double heals. I don't regard 'making tanks feel secure' as a valid reason -- if they feel insecure and get the heal, they're wimps in my book. If they feel insecure and don't get the heal, what are they going to do? Run? HAW HAW HAW. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ujarnin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jarnin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 5:51:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.interofficenetworks.com/demo/doh/sigpic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Subject Needed... I think? All these blasted re: blank s</span><hr size=1> Actually, I'd rather not have it shown all the time. Instead, I wish there was a way to refer to a line in the chat box with a simple % command. For instance, for your last spell cast, you could say the Spell message that you recieve from a casting.<br>
<br>
Like %nm would quote the last non-melee damage message you got. That way you could set up better macros. for instance, you could macro;<br>
<br>
a mature cromodrac' was hit by non-melee for 1120 points of damage.<br>
<br>
like this:<br>
<br>
/g %nm<br>
<br>
where %nm would be the message, and since you started with /g, it'd say to the group &quot;a mature cromodrac' was hit by non-melee for 1120 points of damage.&quot;<br>
<br>
It'd only work off your last reported non-melee damage, so you could report resists, or full hits. It would be very useful for other things as well.<br>
<br>
For instance, if there were a %auction command, you could either report your auctions, or by using %auction &lt;playername&gt; you could report another players auction to your group, guild, or whoever.<br>
<br>
I don't want macros that make fighting easier, I want macros that will enable me to communicate better in game. Afterall, this would probably free up alot of the /ooc channels and /shout channels on raids.<br>
<br>
There are so many different % commands they could put in, it's scary. I just hope they do it someday. <p><center><br>Jarnin Fisheermann<Br><b>Disciple of Hate<Br><b>Rallos Zek</b><Br></b><Br>Grand Master Fisherman<Br>Master Brewer<Br>Master Chef<Br>Master of Begging<Br><Br><b>DEATH TO AL`KABOR!</b></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uzhaun.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zhaun</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 7:36:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Subject Needed... I think? All these blasted re: blank s</span><hr size=1> <br>
More spam makes baby jebus cry... also this would just be turned off by everyone just like melee hits are.<br>
<br>
Other than that, I'd rather not see it reported 'casue I don't want to people see how little damage I do somtimes. Sure sometimes I can whip out the big guns and own somthing, but ussually I don't contribute too much to the group damage per mob.<br>
<br>
I think adding our damage output to normal combat spam would get us laughed at more than congratulated... 'casue they only people who may keep it on are people who want to make fun of us hehehe <p>-Zhaun<BR>Evoker of Torv</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utheperfectflaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ThePerfectFlaw</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/jolly.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 8:59:28 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.theperfectflaw.com/picture/jolly.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Subject Needed... I think? All these blasted re: blank s</span><hr size=1> It's not necessary info.  I suppose if they ever put in critical casts, they'll include that.<br>
<br>
Thing is though, people know if you're nuking or not.  If that damn cerulean sky gazer gates, you weren't nuking. <p><hr>
The Wizard formerly known as Zehn Druidbane
<br>
Nicholas, 'The Perfect Flaw'
<br>
"Any sufficiently advanced technology is indistinguishable from a rigged demo."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uyockbo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>yockbo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 10:08:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re :</span><hr size=1> Just my 2 cents.<br>
<br>
I love to see macro's when something gets snared, charmed malaised or whatever. This helps me and other group members immensely. sometimes one misses the text that shows on the screen when say somethign is snared. <br>
<br>
As far as screaming out how much damage I do with a macro is a waste of time IMO. It clutters the chat window with something that isn't necessary.  If you feel you need to tell your group how much you are doing then your group need to wkae up. I don't see too many tanks taking away half a mobs health with one swing of their migty sword.<br>
<br>
Anyways that's just my opinion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/umysthyl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mysthyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/14/01 11:14:31 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> spell damage</span><hr size=1> If you want your spell damage reported to everyone then you need to go play a rogue or monk for a bit. I have both and definately DON'T want my spell damage reported for all to laugh at. The only possible exception would be banes. If you know how to use them and survive the damage is definately impressive. <br>
<br>
Mysthyl<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ueindyinromenril.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eindyin Romenril</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 2:44:43 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://eindyin.homestead.com/files/einphoto.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1> If this was set up, my cover would be blown... no more casting level 12 DDs to make it look like i'm doing something!<br>
<br>
