<br>
The melee's never notice what we are doing... but the clerics do.<br>
<br>
For a wizard, grouping is a privilege that I could care less about.  Grouped I get 1 yellow per hour.  Ungrouped, it's 1 yellow per 1 1/2 hour to 2 hours.  Just takes me twice longer to level ungrouped.  In the long run, that's a level per 5 hours grouped, 1 level per 10 ours ungrouped... OUCH.<br>
<br>
Was on DL the other day.  A melee heavy group with 1 cleric had a monk leaving.  They /ooc'd looking for more so I sent them a tell.  So I sit there do my usual nuke and med thing, stay under the agro radar.  About 10 minutes later cleric sends me a tell asking me what I'm nuking for.  I told him I'm doing around 600 dmg per mob and that I could do more but that seems to be sufficient enough for this group.  What I didn't tell him was I was throwing stuns as well which makes quite a bit of difference on a mobs damage output.  A few more minutes later he sends me a tell again thanking me for joining the group.<br>
<br>
Well whoa is me... the wizzy who has never LFG'd since level 33 and solo'd mostly till 44 is being thanked by a cleric for joining their group.  A bit flattered... yes.  I just never thought I'd see the day that I could be a factor in a group.  But of course, only the cleric realizes this I guess it's because he was probably finally able to see a full mana bar.  The melee's do their own thing not noticing the benefits of having a level 44 wizard in their group.  I could care less at that point whether melee's notice or not.<br>
<br>
So 1 hour of grouping and I get my 1 yellow bubble, I decide it's time for me to move on because I just saved myself an hour of experiencing solo.  Time to meet up with friends and do some adventuring.  Did a /g I'll be going in a few... please start looking for a replacement.  Cleric sends me a tell again verifying if I'm really going.  Told him yes, then he says he's going too.  I told him he better tell the group.  He did... and that pretty much killed the group.<br>
<br>
I never realized up to that day how much of a manna drain for 1 cleric 4 melees are.  I never really knew how nervous a cleric gets when manna starts getting low with 3 mezzed drolvargs waiting to be killed(wizards just quad kite those buggers).  I was always under the impression that 1 cleric can keep 4 melees alive (also had 1 chanter that gave me clarity which made nuking much sweeter).  Maybe this was true from level 1 thru 40 with 5 uber twinked melees.  But in the 40's specially in the Dreadlands, where the Drolvargs hit for 108 every second... it doesn't matter what gear you have.  They will still eat you up and own you.  That's when class diversity begins to play a role.<br>
<br>
I could care less about showing my damage.  My presence in that group was felt only by one class, the cleric.  And frankly, that's the only class that needs to know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utorcerarcana.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Torcer Arcana</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(8/15/01 6:44:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: They need to see the damage we Wizzy's do!</span><hr size=1>      Give us the choice to keep it on or off.  That way, everyone is happy.  And as for the whole &quot;VI wants to keep Magical Damage mysterious&quot; that is so ridiculous as to not even warrant my commentary. <p>Torcer Arcana<Br>Level 55 Wizard<Br>The Nameless</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=6227.topic&start=21&stop=26>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6243.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessage?topicID=6224.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.emailToFriend?topicID=6227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.threadControl?topicID=6227.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.